From: conda-forge
Subject: [PATCH] Build position-independent code on all architectures

The fPIC check only matched x86_64 and the macOS "arm64" spelling of the
processor; on others (notably Linux "aarch64") it fell through to
${CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE}, which is unset by default and expands to an
empty string, so Hammer_PIC became empty and every set_target_properties(...
POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE ${Hammer_PIC} ...) failed with "incorrect number of
arguments". The libraries are archived into the shared pyHammer module, so
default to PIC on every architecture while still honouring an explicitly set
CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE.
---
--- a/CMakeModules/CompilerChecks.cmake
+++ b/CMakeModules/CompilerChecks.cmake
@@ -53,15 +53,18 @@
 endif()
 
 # setting fPIC
-message(STATUS "${CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR}")
+# All Hammer libraries can be archived into the shared pyHammer bindings module,
+# so default to position-independent code on every architecture; honour an
+# explicit CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE when one is provided. The previous
+# x86_64/arm64 allow-list left Hammer_PIC empty on other processors (e.g.
+# aarch64), which broke the set_target_properties() calls that consume it.
+if(DEFINED CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE)
+    set(Hammer_PIC ${CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE})
+else()
+    set(Hammer_PIC TRUE)
+endif()
 
-IF(CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR STREQUAL "x86_64" OR CMAKE_SYSTEM_PROCESSOR STREQUAL "arm64")
-    set(Hammer_PIC TRUE)
-ELSE()
-    set(Hammer_PIC ${CMAKE_POSITION_INDEPENDENT_CODE})
-ENDIF()
-
-message(STATUS "Process independent code flag is ${Hammer_PIC}.")
+message(STATUS "Position independent code flag is ${Hammer_PIC}.")
 
 IF(NOT CMAKE_CONFIGURATION_TYPES AND NOT CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE)
     SET(CMAKE_BUILD_TYPE Release CACHE STRING
